"author_information": "Oscar Wilde (1854-1900) was an Irish poet, playwright, and novelist known for his wit, aesthetic philosophy, and flamboyant style. His works often challenged Victorian social norms and explored themes of beauty, morality, and decadence.",
"interesting_fact": "The initial publication of 'The Picture of Dorian Gray' in Lippincott's Monthly Magazine in 1890 was met with significant controversy due to its perceived immorality. Wilde later revised and expanded the novel, adding a preface and several chapters to address the criticism and further explore his aesthetic philosophy."
